De_Rats by RomeoJGuy
--------------------

*Thank You for Downloading*

This is a port of the de_rats map from CS1.6, but instead of just taking the old map and decompiling it
and going from there I built everything by hand. Here is a rundown of the updates:
*The window actually has an outside thanks to 3d skyboxes.
*The fridge recieved upgrades of snowy and displacement mapped ground.
*The Water is updated to CSS standards.
*All objects are physicsable meaning lots of different interesting kills
*Clock can be shot off the wall and smash you.
*Added more sponges to the sponge tub to allow for fights on there.
*Updated the bug spray with new source effects.
*Oven uses new source heat wave effects and is now accessible in the oven. (It requires a master jumper, and will hurt you to get there)
*Cabinet has been upgraded with new items like a box of nails and a marble trap.

I am sure you will enjoy. I know the pre-sdk people have. Thanks.


HOW TO INSTALL:

Place the folders into your

xxx\Valve\Steam\SteamApps\usernameXXX\counter-strike source\cstrike\

The materials folder contains the necessary material files.

The maps folder contains the de_rats.bsp

Enjoy =)


http://romeojguy.com | http://www.hl2world.com | http://www.unclestupid.com

This map was made with Hammer world editor for CSS, Gmod, HL2DM and any other game utilizing the Source engine.

The creator of this map is Christopher L. Doucette
The last name is pronound Do-Set for all you idiots out there.
I also go by ZeldaFN and DevoutFollowerOfTheWeasel

The custom textures are by the same person. Everything was scanned by a conventional scanner. Yes, even the wall was scanned with the same conventional scanner. I just tilted the printer/scanner sideway to the wall and scanned.

The skybox textures are not mine. The skybox is from PVK II used in their map called pvk_island. PVK II is a mod, a damn awesome mod if you ask me Bob. I borrowed the texture without permission, but I'm sure no one will care.

The BSP is a fast mode compile. That means VIS and RAD were compiled in fast mode. HDR was not enabled. I know that sucks, but I included the VMF.
This means you can change or add to the map. You can beautify it more, fix any bugs you find, make the lighting better than the crap I have now. Most importantly, you can recompile in normal mode for better quality, with HDR for that nifty lighting effect that makes any map look sexy.

You can contact me to make any of your updates official and I'll re-release the map with them and credit you for your hard work.

De_5th_ave made by Ziu

###

Story:

At a time when 5cm tall people live in the 5th Avenue
they founded their own religion and lived in peace 
and harmony, but there appeared a new alliance and 
disturb the harmony.


###


T: Destroy the shipmodel on the bed.
Ct: Dont let them destroy our Oracle!!

All textures and models are custom except for,
closet_clothes.vtf & clothes.mdl
That is simply a stock Valve model rescaled by me, for Rats.

The Amiga 1000, Yamaha DX7, Turntable, NES, Quilt model and All brush work belong to me; Christopher Doucette aka DIFTOW.

Majority of textures are photographs or scans from me, and some feature intense editing or completely computer generated content (not from photo/scan).

----

95% of everything was based on real world measurement data; 1/16th of an inch measurement accuracy, rounded to Hammer grid.

The most proportionally correct Rats map ever made.

The scale is 19x, which is smaller than most Rats map I've played, so you won't find this to be too gigantic. High places are limited, so sniping should be less of an annoyance in this map compared with some of the other top maps.
